        <p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong><br /> He attended Roman Catholic Mission (RCM) Primary School, Shendam (1977); Government Secondary School Shendam (1982); School of Preliminary Studies Keffi (1986); Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria (1990); The Nigerian Law School Lagos (1991) and University of Jos (2006) and obtained the qualifications of Elementary School Certificate, GCE O’Level, IJMB A’ Level, Bachelor of Law (LL.B), Barrister at Law (BL) and Master in Law (LL.M) respectively.</p>
        
        <p><strong>PROFESSIONAL AND PUBLIC SERVICE EXPERIENCES:</strong> <br /> After the mandatory National Youth Service Corp (NYSC) in the Legal Unit of FCDA Abuja, he started professional career in 1992 with the prestigious T- Obot & Co. Legal Practitioners, Jos. He also Worked with Victor Fomwul & Co. Jos from 1997-1999 as a Managing Partner, before establishing his Firm, Simon B. Lalong & Co. Legal Practitioners as the Principal Partner. He held several positions of responsibility, which included Assistant Secretary, Nigeria Bar Association, Plateau State Chapter from 1992 to 1994 and the National President of Goemai Youth Movement that same period.</p>
        
        <p>
            <strong>POLITICAL CAREER:</strong> At the twilight of return to democratic governance in 1998, and as a youth activist/Lawyer, his early political career was active participation in the formation of the people’s Democratic Party (PDP) at the grassroots in Shendam L.G.A. In 1999, contested and won election into the Plateau State House of Assembly (Served 2 terms). Within one year in the House, had served as Chairman, House Committee on Judiciary; Member, House Committee on Local Government & Chieftaincy Affairs, Public Accounts/Petition and Agriculture. <br />  <br />

            By October 2000, in recognition of his leadership traits he was unanimously elected Honourable Speaker of the Plateau State House of Assembly and by divine intervention earned the record of the longest serving Speaker in the history of Plateau state legislature for seven years of unbroken leadership (2000 – 2006).  As a Member and a Speaker, he is proud to be associated with the following landmark achievements, which led to the establishment of the following tertiary institutions: Plateau State University, Bokkos; College of Agriculture Garkawa; College of Arts, Science and Remedial Studies, Kurgwi. Similarly, he sponsored Bills on Creation of additional/new Chiefdoms, Districts and State Electoral Wards as well as Private Bill on establishment of structures in Local Government Councils. As Speaker, he endeared myself to fellow Speakers across the 36 states in Nigeria and was elected twice as Chairman, Nigerian Conference of Speakers (i.e. forum of all the 36 Speakers of the Federation) from 2001-2002. This led to laying a solid foundation of the forum. He is the National Chairman, Forum of All Former Speakers of Nigeria (COFSSHA) and Chairman of Former State Legislators, Plateau State Chapter.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>LALONG AS GOVERNOR AND HIS VISION AND MISSION:</strong> Governor Lalong was voted and sworn in as 5th Executive Governor of Plateau State on 29th May 2015. The stunningly beautiful Plateau State is the Home of Peace, Tourism and Hospitality; a national asset endowed with great human and material resources; a wealth of resources and a wealth of opportunities for present and future development. Assertive without unnecessarily being too uncompromising, Governor Lalong is a patriot who has offered himself to serve with loyalty, humility, diligence, without prejudice to religion and ethnicity. His underlying philosophical approach is being ‘people oriented and people-centered’ for a peaceful, united and prosperous State where all youths and elders are free to express their talents. His Vision and Mission for the state is fundamentally about Service and fairness in distribution of scarce resources and developmental projects across the geo-political zones of the state. Above all, his cognate experience and exposure as the longest serving speaker of the Plateau State House of Assembly and a witness to workings of the Legislature, Executive, Judiciary and crisis management genuinely prepared him from the early years in sustainable integration and governance. 
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>AS EXECUTIVE GOVERNOR</strong> he is a member of the National Council of States, National Economic Council, Nigerian Governors Forum, Progressive Governors Forum. He also holds several positions of responsibility, namely, Committee on Review of Minimum Wage, Presidential Food Security Council. Just recently, this great personality was unanimously elected and inaugurated as Chairman of the Northern Governors Forum, where in the coming years (2019 – 2023), he will diligently lead the 19 Northern States Governors, given the believe and trust in uncommon capacity for exhibiting duty of care to all and sundry.
        </p>
